There are several ways to register a license, depending on its type and use case: 

using the Register dialog of  (the most common case)
          to register a named-user based or concurrent license;

storing the license key into a file (either text or xml) that is copied to the
          installation directory of .

At start-up, looks for a valid license key in the following locations, in this order:
in the xml file registration;
in the text file registration;
in its internal settings files created after you used the Register dialog to validate a named-user based or concurrent licenseor concurrent licence.
